en_6804049_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – The police has cracked down on an illegal hashish trafficking business that smuggled the drug from Italy.
en_6804049_1	The police said that the drug was brought to the country by air courier by tactfully concealing it in electrical equipment.
en_6804049_2	The haul of hashish weighed 600g.
en_6804049_3	The stock had reportedly been smuggled to residents in Kuliyapitiya and Negombo.
en_6804049_4	Three suspects of ages 29, 41 and 46 have been taken into custody over the incident.
en_6804049_5	They have been identified as residents of Munamaldeniya, Horana, and Minuwangoda.
en_6804049_6	A television and 05 mobile phones that were also smuggled along with the drugs were seized from the suspects’ possession.
